# Architecture & Module Layout

## Repo Structure
```
/
├── backend/              # Python — FastAPI + quant core
│   ├── app/              # FastAPI application
│   │   ├── main.py       # App entry point, CORS, lifespan
│   │   └── routers/      # Route modules (market, strategies, etc.)
│   ├── quant/            # Core quant library (importable package)
│   │   ├── data/         # Market data sources and abstractions
│   │   ├── strategies/   # Strategy base class + implementations
│   │   ├── backtesting/  # Backtest engine
│   │   ├── execution/    # Broker interfaces (Alpaca, paper, etc.)
│   │   ├── risk/         # Cost models: fees, slippage, latency
│   │   ├── metrics/      # Performance metrics (Sharpe, drawdown, etc.)
│   │   └── sentiment/    # LLM/Perplexity sentiment integration
│   └── pyproject.toml
├── frontend/             # Next.js App Router + shadcn/ui
│   ├── app/              # Pages and layouts
│   ├── components/       # Reusable UI components
│   └── lib/              # API client, utilities
├── context/              # Living wiki — MUST be kept updated
└── .cursor/rules/        # AI agent guidance — self-maintained
```

## Boundaries
- **All quant math, data fetching, and order logic lives in `backend/quant/`.** Never put trading logic in API routers or frontend.
- **API routers are thin** — validate inputs, call `quant/`, return shaped responses. No business logic.
- **Frontend is display + interaction only.** No trading decisions. Calls `backend` via REST.
- **New data sources** go in `quant/data/` implementing `MarketDataSource` base.
- **New strategies** go in `quant/strategies/` implementing `BaseStrategy`.
- **New broker integrations** go in `quant/execution/` implementing `BaseBroker`.

## Local Development
- Backend: `cd backend && uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload` → `http://127.0.0.1:8000`
- Frontend: `cd frontend && npm run dev` → `http://localhost:3000`
- Frontend talks to backend via `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000`

## Production Targets (future — not built yet)
- UI → Vercel
- Engine + API → GCP Cloud Run (`min-instances=1`, always-warm)
- Scheduler → GCP Cloud Scheduler
- Logs → GCP Cloud Logging
- DB → TBD (Neon Postgres or Cloud SQL), behind a thin interface
